parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling or shutting down can cause loss of power, loss of control, and accidents, especially when occurring at high speeds.
symptoms: Engine stalling or shutting down without warning
often when coming to a stop or accelerating at low speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft position sensor can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and difficulty starting the engine, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The engine noise or tapping can indicate internal engine damage, which can lead to engine failure, loss of power, and accidents.
symptoms: Tapping or knocking noise from the engine
especially when starting the engine in cold weather.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the camshaft positioning sensor can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and difficulty starting the engine, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Engine failure or internal damage can cause loss of power, loss of control, and accidents, especially when occurring at high speeds.
Water pump failure can cause engine overheating, loss of power, and accidents, especially when occurring at high speeds.
Fumes or exhaust issues can cause health problems, nausea, vomiting, and allergic reactions, especially for passengers with pre-existing health conditions.
symptoms: rusting of the rear of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering assist can cause loss of steering control, making it difficult to maneuver the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
